{"_id":"jY8z91yk599r1Bqt","name":"Shadow Hunter","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/light/projectile-beam-yellow-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"XjfIUSoxxTbqvCms","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","scenarioSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","sourceDirectory":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","contentKey":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.shadow-hunter","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have learned the weakness of Sherazade's Shadows—those OL 5, 1 Wound copies of past enemies with Shadow Body Gifts. Shadows can appear and disappear from darkness (+1 OL in shadows), regenerate unless in full light, and are only permanently destroyed by direct sunlight. With this Gift: (1) You can force Shadows to manifest by creating bright light (lanterns, magic, fire)—they cannot use Shadow Body while you illuminate them. (2) Once per Scene, make an opposed Check vs a Shadow's OL 5: on success, you've maneuvered it into a sunbeam, moonbeam through window, or reflected light—Shadow is destroyed permanently without Wound roll. (3) You recognize which past enemy a Shadow is copying, giving you +1 to Checks against it based on previous knowledge of its tactics.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Survive at least one encounter with Sherazade's Shadows and study their mechanics, OR research shadow-creature lore</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Requires light source to be effective—useless in total darkness. Creating bright light may alert other enemies. Sunlight destruction only works if you can create/find actual sunlight (challenging indoors or at night). Some locations Sherazade chooses for confrontations have no windows or light sources—plan accordingly.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> combat, light, knowledge, anti-shadow</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - One Thousand and One Nightmares","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.shadow-hunter","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","scenarioSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","sourceDirectory":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","tags":["combat","light","knowledge","anti-shadow"],"requirements":"Survive at least one encounter with Sherazade's Shadows and study their mechanics, OR research shadow-creature lore","limitations":"Requires light source to be effective—useless in total darkness. Creating bright light may alert other enemies. Sunlight destruction only works if you can create/find actual sunlight (challenging indoors or at night). Some locations Sherazade chooses for confrontations have no windows or light sources—plan accordingly."},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332107,"modifiedTime":1784280332107,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"w4lZSFYdxVIBJCAi","name":"Story Breaker","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-pentagon-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":"XjfIUSoxxTbqvCms","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","scenarioSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","sourceDirectory":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","contentKey":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.story-breaker","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>Sherazade traps victims inside stories—either locking them in narrative loops where they relive false memories, or creating 'what-if' scenarios that never happened. You've learned to recognize when you're inside a story rather than reality. Watch for narrative inconsistencies: characters acting wrong, impossible events, details that don't match your memories. Once per Scene when trapped in a story, make a Mental Check vs Sherazade's OL 7: on success, you break the narrative—story shatters like glass and you return to reality, immune to story imprisonment for rest of Scene. On failure, you're deeper in the story and must find its 'ending' before you can escape (GM creates story-specific exit condition). You can also attempt to free ONE other trapped victim when you break out.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Be trapped in at least one of Sherazade's stories and escape, OR witness someone else trapped and deduce the pattern</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Requires Mental Check each time—repeated story trapping becomes harder to break. Some stories are more seductive than reality (what-if where loved one never died)—GM may impose disadvantage if story offers something you desperately want. Breaking story while others remain trapped may anger them (they don't realize it's false). Sherazade adapts—after you break first story, her subsequent stories are more complex (higher OL or multiple layers).</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> mental, escape, anti-narrative, reality</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - One Thousand and One Nightmares","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.story-breaker","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","scenarioSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","sourceDirectory":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","tags":["mental","escape","anti-narrative","reality"],"requirements":"Be trapped in at least one of Sherazade's stories and escape, OR witness someone else trapped and deduce the pattern","limitations":"Requires Mental Check each time—repeated story trapping becomes harder to break. Some stories are more seductive than reality (what-if where loved one never died)—GM may impose disadvantage if story offers something you desperately want. Breaking story while others remain trapped may anger them (they don't realize it's false). Sherazade adapts—after you break first story, her subsequent stories are more complex (higher OL or multiple layers)."},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332107,"modifiedTime":1784280332107,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"AD7wd0giBZ2DeKpB","name":"Truth Beneath Tales","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-tendrils-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":"XjfIUSoxxTbqvCms","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","scenarioSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","sourceDirectory":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","contentKey":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.truth-beneath-tales","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>Sherazade's Gift 'Words like Honey' makes her incredibly persuasive and believable—people trust her instinctively, follow her suggestions, believe her lies. You've learned to see through her narrative manipulation by focusing on actions rather than words. When Sherazade or her Shadows attempt social manipulation, persuasion, or deception against you, you gain +2 to resist (effectively reducing her OL from 7 to 5 for Social Checks targeting you). Additionally, once per Scene, you can point out a contradiction in her story to one NPC: make a Social Check vs her OL 7—on success, that NPC becomes immune to her Words like Honey for this Scene and may turn against her. This represents your ability to find truth buried beneath beautiful lies.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Recognize Sherazade's Words like Honey Gift in action and study how she manipulates others, OR resist her manipulation successfully at least once</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Only protects YOU from social manipulation—allies remain vulnerable unless you spend action to free them. Pointing out contradictions may anger Sherazade, causing her to abandon subtlety and attack directly. Some NPCs are so deeply manipulated they refuse to believe evidence even when presented clearly. This Gift doesn't work against her other powers (story imprisonment, Shadow summoning)—only social manipulation.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> social, perception, anti-manipulation, truth</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - One Thousand and One Nightmares","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","source":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.one-thousand-and-one-nightmares.truth-beneath-tales","scenario":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","scenarioSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","sourceDirectory":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","tags":["social","perception","anti-manipulation","truth"],"requirements":"Recognize Sherazade's Words like Honey Gift in action and study how she manipulates others, OR resist her manipulation successfully at least once","limitations":"Only protects YOU from social manipulation—allies remain vulnerable unless you spend action to free them. Pointing out contradictions may anger Sherazade, causing her to abandon subtlety and attack directly. Some NPCs are so deeply manipulated they refuse to believe evidence even when presented clearly. This Gift doesn't work against her other powers (story imprisonment, Shadow summoning)—only social manipulation."},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332108,"modifiedTime":1784280332108,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"uL2ZEbbMpHA3XJpO","name":"Companion's Transformation","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/light/explosion-star-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":"pIiydn6zzuUzcVFb","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.companion-s-transformation","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have befriended one of OZena's three companions (Lowe, Hirnloser, or Dose) and witnessed their character arc complete: the coward finding courage, the 'brainless' proving genius, or the hollow finding heart through love. Their transformation inspires you. Choose one companion you've built relationship with. Once per scenario, channel their realized virtue: **Lowe's Courage** (reroll any Fear/Intimidation Check, taking better result), **Hirnloser's Genius** (ask GM one specific tactical question—'What's the hidden weakness?' 'What would genius do?'—and receive honest answer), or **Dose's Love** (when protecting someone you care for, +2 to Defense or one automatic success on Protect action). This gift represents how witnessing others' growth helps us find our own strength.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Build meaningful relationship with at least one companion across multiple Parts, witness or facilitate their Part Three transformation</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Can only channel virtue of companion you've actually befriended—can't choose all three. If that companion dies or betrays you before their arc completes, lose this gift. Using this gift in their presence grants them +1 to their next Check (your faith empowers them).</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> inspiration, character-development, virtue, social</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.companion-s-transformation","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["inspiration","character-development","virtue","social"],"requirements":"Build meaningful relationship with at least one companion across multiple Parts, witness or facilitate their Part Three transformation","limitations":"Can only channel virtue of companion you've actually befriended—can't choose all three. If that companion dies or betrays you before their arc completes, lose this gift. Using this gift in their presence grants them +1 to their next Check (your faith empowers them)."},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332109,"modifiedTime":1784280332109,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"GT4QBDk1mSqHmcCc","name":"Fragment of the Red Compass","type":"gift","img":"icons/sundries/misc/compass-brass-red-orange.webp","effects":[],"folder":"AYFGFVmRFeBgrRym","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.fragment-of-the-red-compass","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You possess the southern (red) piece of the Compass Rose that Helga guarded. This bloodstone needle pulses like a heartbeat and points toward the nearest Compass Rose piece (now north toward the emerald center piece in Smaragd). While carrying this fragment, you sense the life force of creatures within 30 feet—useful for detecting hidden enemies or determining if someone is dying. Once per Scene, activate the fragment to track one specific person you've met: the needle points toward them for one Scene, even through walls. Warning: this piece is stained with centuries of blood magic—carrying it may attract blood-hungry creatures or cause disturbing visions of Helga's victims.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Obtained from Helga (through combat, negotiation, or inheriting after her death)</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Life-sense is passive but overwhelming in crowded areas. Tracking requires you to have previously met the target. Each additional Compass Rose piece you carry increases the burden—GM may call for Fortitude Checks to resist temporal displacement headaches. Henkle desperately wants this piece.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> temporal, navigation, life-sense, artifact</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.fragment-of-the-red-compass","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["temporal","navigation","life-sense","artifact"],"requirements":"Obtained from Helga (through combat, negotiation, or inheriting after her death)","limitations":"Life-sense is passive but overwhelming in crowded areas. Tracking requires you to have previously met the target. Each additional Compass Rose piece you carry increases the burden—GM may call for Fortitude Checks to resist temporal displacement headaches. Henkle desperately wants this piece."},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332109,"modifiedTime":1784280332109,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Sz1MVwyGSsTCSh5w","name":"Fragment of the Yellow Compass","type":"gift","img":"icons/sundries/misc/compass-brass-blue-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":"RVknfQCDlTRDVfcw","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.fragment-of-the-yellow-compass","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You possess the western (yellow) piece of the Compass Rose that Margareta guarded. This golden needle hums with temporal energy and points toward the nearest Compass Rose piece (currently southeast toward Helga's red piece in Rot). While carrying this fragment, you experience temporal echoes: glimpses of past and future in this location. Once per Scene, consult the fragment to receive a vision—GM reveals one useful fact about the immediate past or near future. Warning: carrying Compass Rose pieces makes you a target for those seeking to control time itself.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Obtained from Margareta (through persuasion, combat, or inheriting after her death)</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Visions are fragmentary and open to interpretation. Fragment grows heavier as you collect more pieces (physical burden of temporal power). Henkle can sense when pieces are brought together.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> temporal, navigation, visions, artifact</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.fragment-of-the-yellow-compass","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["temporal","navigation","visions","artifact"],"requirements":"Obtained from Margareta (through persuasion, combat, or inheriting after her death)","limitations":"Visions are fragmentary and open to interpretation. Fragment grows heavier as you collect more pieces (physical burden of temporal power). Henkle can sense when pieces are brought together."},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332110,"modifiedTime":1784280332110,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"XbPdVtc82w8iYnlW","name":"Infusion of Purity","type":"gift","img":"icons/consumables/potions/potion-bottle-corked-labeled-green.webp","effects":[],"folder":"AYFGFVmRFeBgrRym","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.infusion-of-purity","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have learned Wolfgang's secret recipe to break blood magic: **Infusion of Purity** requires burdock root (courage), nettle (protection), hyssop (purification), and **elderberry** (life). When you spend 1 Increment preparing and consuming this infusion, you gain immunity to blood magic for one Scene: Helga cannot control your blood, puppet you if wounded, or drain your life force. Additionally, if Helga is wounded while you have active Infusion in your system and your blood touches her, it acts as poison—negating her Blood Witch regeneration and causing her to age rapidly. This infusion represents nature's power to cleanse corruption. Wolfgang grows these herbs in his secret greenhouse—you must either rescue him or find his hidden garden.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Rescue Wolfgang from blood servitude and learn his recipe, OR discover his hidden greenhouse and decipher his botanical notes</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Requires 1 Increment to prepare and consume. Ingredients must be fresh—dried herbs lose potency. Only works against blood magic, not other supernatural threats. Effect lasts one Scene (30-60 minutes). Elderberry is the rare component—Wolfgang may have limited supply.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> consumable, protection, anti-magic, crafting</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.infusion-of-purity","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["consumable","protection","anti-magic","crafting"],"requirements":"Rescue Wolfgang from blood servitude and learn his recipe, OR discover his hidden greenhouse and decipher his botanical notes","limitations":"Requires 1 Increment to prepare and consume. Ingredients must be fresh—dried herbs lose potency. Only works against blood magic, not other supernatural threats. Effect lasts one Scene (30-60 minutes). Elderberry is the rare component—Wolfgang may have limited supply."},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332111,"modifiedTime":1784280332111,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"hddjeFaOep6cLGNo","name":"Manycorpses' Tragedy","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/death/skull-horned-worn-white.webp","effects":[],"folder":"AYFGFVmRFeBgrRym","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.manycorpses-tragedy","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You witnessed or learned the tragic story of Manycorpses—two lovers fused by Helga's blood magic into a monstrous form, forced to serve the witch who destroyed them. This knowledge has hardened your resolve against blood magic's corruption and taught you about the power of love even in monstrous forms. Once per scenario, when facing a creature or person transformed by dark magic, you can attempt to reach their humanity: make a Social Check opposed by their Opposition Level. On success, they hesitate for one Exchange (losing their action), or if they were once good, they may actively help you for one Scene before the magic reasserts control. This represents your ability to see the person beneath the monster.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Witness Manycorpses' tragedy, learn their story from servants, OR speak with them and recognize their suffering</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Only works on beings who were once fully human/humane and transformed against their will. Does not work on creatures who chose corruption or were always monstrous. The transformed being suffers greatly when fighting their compulsion—using this gift is merciful but painful for them.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> social, empathy, anti-corruption, monster-humanization</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village.manycorpses-tragedy","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Two: The Red Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-two-the-red-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["social","empathy","anti-corruption","monster-humanization"],"requirements":"Witness Manycorpses' tragedy, learn their story from servants, OR speak with them and recognize their suffering","limitations":"Only works on beings who were once fully human/humane and transformed against their will. Does not work on creatures who chose corruption or were always monstrous. The transformed being suffers greatly when fighting their compulsion—using this gift is merciful but painful for them."},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332111,"modifiedTime":1784280332111,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TQK7AiJnBbs6DFnF","name":"Sanctuary of Gelb","type":"gift","img":"icons/environment/settlement/house-small.webp","effects":[],"folder":"RVknfQCDlTRDVfcw","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.sanctuary-of-gelb","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have earned the trust and gratitude of the outcasts in the village of Gelb. The villagers—people with leontiasis, elephantiasis, severe burns, missing limbs—see you as protector rather than threat. While in Gelb, you have sanctuary: free lodging, meals, basic medical care. Villagers warn you of dangers, share rumors about Rot and Smaragd, offer their unique skills. Once per scenario, call upon a villager's specialized knowledge (herbalism, tracking, local history). If Margareta survived, she provides magical insight. If she died protecting them, they honor you as her successor and will risk their lives to help you stop Henkle.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Save Klaus from kidnappers, show compassion to outcasts, or defeat those threatening Gelb</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Villagers are not warriors—they provide support, not combat aid. If you betray their trust or harm them, lose this gift permanently. Henkle or OZena may target Gelb to hurt you.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> social, sanctuary, allies, knowledge</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.sanctuary-of-gelb","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["social","sanctuary","allies","knowledge"],"requirements":"Save Klaus from kidnappers, show compassion to outcasts, or defeat those threatening Gelb","limitations":"Villagers are not warriors—they provide support, not combat aid. If you betray their trust or harm them, lose this gift permanently. Henkle or OZena may target Gelb to hurt you."},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332112,"modifiedTime":1784280332112,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CbZeN5CDCV4UOWx8","name":"The Wishing Well's Price","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/water/barrier-ice-crystal-wall-jagged-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"pIiydn6zzuUzcVFb","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.the-wishing-well-s-price","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have learned the truth about Smaragd's Wishing Well: it grants wishes, but corrupts them in cruel ways. The villagers prove this—one wished for wealth and became living gold statue, another for eternal beauty and became porcelain doll, another to never sleep and went mad from exhaustion. You can make ONE wish at the well, but you understand the price. Before wishing, make a Check vs OL Hard (7): on success, phrase your wish carefully enough that corruption is minimized (GM interprets fairly but still with consequence). On failure, wish is granted in most twisted way possible. Alternatively, use your knowledge to resist the well's temptation: once per Scene, when an NPC or enemy tries to use the well, you can intervene and explain the cost—make Social Check to convince them. This represents wisdom to see through false promises.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Investigate the Villagers of Emerald and learn their wish-corruption stories, OR witness Henkle or enemy using the well</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>You can only make ONE wish per campaign—choose wisely. If you wish for something selfless (helping others, stopping Henkle, saving companions), GM should minimize corruption. Selfish wishes corrupt more severely. The well cannot grant impossible wishes (resurrection, time travel without Compass Rose, true love). Some villagers may become hostile if you try to destroy their 'gift' even if it's a curse.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> knowledge, temptation, wishes, wisdom</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.the-wishing-well-s-price","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["knowledge","temptation","wishes","wisdom"],"requirements":"Investigate the Villagers of Emerald and learn their wish-corruption stories, OR witness Henkle or enemy using the well","limitations":"You can only make ONE wish per campaign—choose wisely. If you wish for something selfless (helping others, stopping Henkle, saving companions), GM should minimize corruption. Selfish wishes corrupt more severely. The well cannot grant impossible wishes (resurrection, time travel without Compass Rose, true love). Some villagers may become hostile if you try to destroy their 'gift' even if it's a curse."},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332112,"modifiedTime":1784280332112,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9q1trYho9gtRdi6U","name":"Time Thief","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/time/hourglass-tilted-gray.webp","effects":[],"folder":"pIiydn6zzuUzcVFb","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.time-thief","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have learned Henkle's secret: his Hot-Air Balloon is powered by Time Tokens harvested from temporal anomalies caused by the Compass Rose's presence in 1780. You can disrupt his escape plan by stealing or destroying his Time Tokens. Once per Scene, when Henkle would gain a Time Token (combat start, delaying him, Hunters lost in Illusory Labyrinth), make a Check vs his OL (5): on success, you intercept the temporal energy—Henkle gains no Token, and you gain insight into time flow (ask GM one yes/no question about immediate future: 'Will the balloon launch this Scene?' 'Is reinforcement arriving?'). If you accumulate 3 Time Tokens before Henkle does, you can either: sabotage his balloon permanently (it will never fly), or redirect the time portal to send companions home instead of Henkle escaping.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Discover Henkle's Time Token mechanic through investigation, eavesdropping, or studying the Hot-Air Balloon</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Henkle notices when Tokens are stolen—he becomes hostile and focuses on eliminating you. Each stolen Token causes temporal headache (GM may impose -1 to Mental Checks while carrying multiple Tokens). If you die while carrying Tokens, they dissipate harmlessly but Henkle can collect new ones. Redirecting time portal requires having both Tokens AND at least two Compass Rose pieces.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> sabotage, temporal, tactical, counter-villain</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village.time-thief","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part Three: The Emerald Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-three-the-emerald-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["sabotage","temporal","tactical","counter-villain"],"requirements":"Discover Henkle's Time Token mechanic through investigation, eavesdropping, or studying the Hot-Air Balloon","limitations":"Henkle notices when Tokens are stolen—he becomes hostile and focuses on eliminating you. Each stolen Token causes temporal headache (GM may impose -1 to Mental Checks while carrying multiple Tokens). If you die while carrying Tokens, they dissipate harmlessly but Henkle can collect new ones. Redirecting time portal requires having both Tokens AND at least two Compass Rose pieces."},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332112,"modifiedTime":1784280332112,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4ArAPLTOTUJnRVBT","name":"Traveler from Tomorrow","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/time/clock-stopwatch-white-gray.webp","effects":[],"folder":"RVknfQCDlTRDVfcw","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.traveler-from-tomorrow","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>Through encounters with OZena, Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose, you've learned they're from the future (early 1900s America). You can recognize anachronistic references: when Hirnloser mentions 'electricity' or Dose talks about 'hospitals,' you understand these are things that don't exist yet in 1780. Once per Scene, leverage your knowledge of their future origin: gain +1 to Social Checks when convincing them you know their secret, recognize which of OZena's behaviors are desperate cries for help versus true malice, identify objects or knowledge that came from their era. This gift represents empathy—understanding they're displaced and suffering, not inherently evil.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Have meaningful conversation with at least one time-displaced character, piece together clues about their origin</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>This knowledge doesn't grant future technology or science. You understand they're from the future but can't replicate their world. Henkle will become hostile if he realizes you know too much.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> knowledge, social, empathy, time-travel</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.traveler-from-tomorrow","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["knowledge","social","empathy","time-travel"],"requirements":"Have meaningful conversation with at least one time-displaced character, piece together clues about their origin","limitations":"This knowledge doesn't grant future technology or science. You understand they're from the future but can't replicate their world. Henkle will become hostile if he realizes you know too much."},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332113,"modifiedTime":1784280332113,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cNPGemSftteSCdBN","name":"Memory of the Dragon","type":"gift","img":"icons/creatures/eyes/lizard-single-slit-pink.webp","effects":[],"folder":"ZsYyFqntb2CyQJos","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","scenarioSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","sourceDirectory":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","contentKey":"scenario-gift.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer.memory-of-the-dragon","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have discovered the truth about Saint George's past—that his friendship with the Dragon was real, that the plague was orchestrated, and that the entire tragedy was manipulated by the One Who Plots in the Shadows. This terrible knowledge has awakened something within you: the memory of the Dragon's perspective. Once per Session, you can spend 2 Soma to access the Dragon's ancient wisdom. For the rest of the Scene, you gain the Descriptor **'I remember what the Dragon knew about ancient laws and betrayals.'** This grants you knowledge about: the true nature of binding oaths and ancient laws, how to recognize manipulation by the One Who Plots, the history of conflict between humans and magical creatures, and ways to resist corruption. Additionally, while this Descriptor is active, Saint George (if present) will become visibly shaken when you speak with the Dragon's wisdom, reducing his Opposition Level by 1 as his resolve wavers with painful memories.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Saint George the Dragon Slayer","somaCost":2,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","source":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer.memory-of-the-dragon","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","scenarioSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","sourceDirectory":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332113,"modifiedTime":1784280332113,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Comdqj1RdAh0lHHg","name":"Paladin's Oath","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/holy/chalice-glowing-gold-water.webp","effects":[],"folder":"ZsYyFqntb2CyQJos","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","scenarioSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","sourceDirectory":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","contentKey":"scenario-gift.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer.paladin-s-oath","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have earned the respect of one of Saint George's Paladins through your actions, and they have shared with you the sacred oath that binds them to their cause. Choose one of the six Paladins you encountered. You gain insight into their special ability and can invoke their spirit once per Scene to aid you. **Trebizond** (create exotic equipment Descriptor, +1 OL when using it), **Demetrius** (take 1 Wound for ally, +1 OL rest of Scene), **Theodore** (inflict 1 Additional Wound when raging, or 1 Wound even on successful Defense), **Martha** (enemies get 2 Penalties when targeting you if other allies present), **Syrus** (negate one Hunter Gift effect per Scene), or **Margaret** (gain +1 OL for each Wound Saint George has suffered). You can only invoke the chosen Paladin's power once per Scene, and it lasts for a single action. The Paladin you choose reflects your own values and fighting style.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Saint George the Dragon Slayer","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","source":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer.paladin-s-oath","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","scenarioSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","sourceDirectory":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332114,"modifiedTime":1784280332114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"3T3AQy5hzxrlzKT4","name":"The Saint's Blessing","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/holy/angel-winged-humanoid-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"ZsYyFqntb2CyQJos","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","scenarioSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","sourceDirectory":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","contentKey":"scenario-gift.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer.the-saint-s-blessing","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>Saint George has recognized your good intentions and blessed you with a fragment of his holy power. Once per Scene, when you would suffer a Wound from a creature with monstrous, magical, or supernatural Descriptors, you can invoke the Saint's protection to reduce the damage. Roll 1 die: on a result of 4-6, you completely avoid the Wound; on 1-3, you still suffer it but gain 1 Additional Success on your next action against that creature. Additionally, you get 1 Additional Success on all Defense Checks against attacks from Dark Presences who serve the One Who Plots in the Shadows, as Saint George's blessing reveals their true nature.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Saint George the Dragon Slayer","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","source":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.saint-george-the-dragon-slayer.the-saint-s-blessing","scenario":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","scenarioSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","sourceDirectory":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332114,"modifiedTime":1784280332114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"NGyYLOAK1DdsnXFW","name":"The Brand of Greed","type":"gift","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-sealed-red-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":"chMlBOssmC7rXGgl","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","contentKey":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.the-brand-of-greed","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>Bardolf Greed has granted you The Brand of Greed, a special pass that marks you as one of his trusted associates. This ornate document bears Bardolf's personal seal and signature, and it is recognized throughout Whitehaven as a symbol of ultimate authority. With The Brand, you get free access to any place in the city—factories, the slaughterhouse, the mine, even Greed's mansion—without anyone being able to object to your entrance. Guards, workers, and officials must comply immediately or face Bardolf's wrath. Additionally, you get 1 Additional Success when you exploit the Brand's importance and Bardolf's backing against any city dweller. Threaten them with Bardolf's displeasure, demand cooperation in his name, or leverage his resources—the Brand makes it clear you speak with his voice. However, carrying The Brand also marks you as an enemy to the Pig Heads and workers' rebellion. Arthur, Frank, and Clarence will see you as Bardolf's agent and tool of oppression.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - The City of Pigs","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The City of Pigs","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.the-brand-of-greed","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332114,"modifiedTime":1784280332114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Kr5YzWnvIv19IFM3","name":"The Meat of The God Under the Mine","type":"gift","img":"icons/consumables/meat/steak-raw-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":"chMlBOssmC7rXGgl","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","contentKey":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.the-meat-of-the-god-under-the-mine","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You possess a piece of the divine flesh torn from The God Under the Mine. The meat regenerates slowly, allowing repeated use. Once per Scene, you can consume a portion of the flesh to temporarily gain supernatural power. When you do, immediately heal 1 Wound and gain 1 Additional Success on all physical actions you take for the rest of that Scene (attacks, climbing, running, lifting, swimming, etc.). The power courses through your body, making you stronger, faster, and more resilient. However, you must wait an entire Scene for the remaining flesh to regenerate before you can use this Gift again. **WARNING:** If you use this Gift in 2 consecutive Scenes without waiting for regeneration, the flesh is completely consumed and you permanently lose this Gift. The temptation to rely on divine power comes with a cost.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - The City of Pigs","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The City of Pigs","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.the-meat-of-the-god-under-the-mine","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332115,"modifiedTime":1784280332115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CDzXDL708mK9obaj","name":"There Is No House That Can Stop Me","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/air/wind-tornado-wall-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":"chMlBOssmC7rXGgl","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","contentKey":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.there-is-no-house-that-can-stop-me","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>**SPECIAL GIFT FOR GAROU THE OLD WOLF ONLY.** Those damned pigs get on your nerves and you can't stand them running away from your wrath. Your primal fury awakens when facing the Browne brothers, channeling the rage of the Big Bad Wolf who could blow down any house. You get 2 Additional Successes when you take action to destroy or overcome any environmental obstacle that stands between you and one of the three Browne brothers who has used their Gang Leader Gift (Arthur, Frank, or Clarence in mutated pig form). This includes: blowing down doors with supernatural breath, smashing through walls, demolishing barricades, collapsing tunnels to create shortcuts, breaking through floors or ceilings, destroying steam engines or machinery used as obstacles, or even collapsing entire buildings if they're hiding inside. Your rage makes the impossible possible—no structure can protect them from you. However, you hate to lose to them. If you have to leave or flee from a Scene without eliminating one of the three pig brothers, your shame and fury cause you to lose 1 Soma immediately. You are the Big Bad Wolf, and pigs cannot escape you.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - The City of Pigs","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The City of Pigs","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.there-is-no-house-that-can-stop-me","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332115,"modifiedTime":1784280332115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9uFVAWuGagRA2DMw","name":"Friend of the Rabbits","type":"gift","img":"icons/creatures/mammals/rabbit-corgi-green-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":"w2iwfAAiKgY8WEii","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","contentKey":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.friend-of-the-rabbits","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have earned the trust of the White Rabbits that carry messages throughout Wonder's impossible architecture. These magical creatures no longer fear you and will approach you willingly. You receive 2 Additional Successes when you attempt to capture or interact with a White Rabbit (reducing the Threat effectively to trivial difficulty). Once you've picked up a White Rabbit and gained its trust, your new little friends will deliver messages for you to any room in Wonder, even through seemingly closed doors, walls, or impossible distances. The rabbits can navigate Wonder's reality-bending structure instinctively, reaching locations that might be inaccessible to Hunters. You can send messages to allies separated in different Cure Rooms, communicate with Hatta Carter in the Basement, or even deliver warnings to Alice Liddell in the Hall of the Mind. The rabbits return to you after delivering their message, bringing back simple yes/no responses or brief replies (up to one sentence) from the recipient.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Wonderbedlam","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Wonderbedlam","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.friend-of-the-rabbits","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332115,"modifiedTime":1784280332115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"A0AJutyCQph26kNN","name":"Lucid Madness","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/perception/eye-tendrils-pink-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":"w2iwfAAiKgY8WEii","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","contentKey":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.lucid-madness","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>After being subjected to Wonder's reality-bending magic, you have begun to understand how madness can be made real. You are slowly figuring out how to make the weirdest ideas manifest through Wonder's impossible architecture. Once per Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to attempt to activate the mad magic of Wonder for your own purposes. State something crazy that you want to accomplish, such as 'I want to walk on walls and ceiling', 'I want my arm to stretch out of proportion to reach that ledge', 'I want to shrink down to fit through that tiny door', 'I want doors to appear where there are only walls', or 'I want time to flow backwards for a moment'. The Storyteller will ask you to make a Position Check with Opposition Level determined by the madness of your request: **OL Easy 3** for minor impossibilities (walking on walls, glowing in the dark), **OL Medium 5** for moderate madness (stretching limbs, changing size), **OL Hard 7** for major reality warping (creating doors, manipulating time, phasing through walls). If you succeed, you gain a temporary Descriptor representing your declared impossibility for the rest of the Scene. If you fail, you have spent your Soma in vain and nothing happens. The effect immediately ends if someone makes it clear that what you are doing is utter madness—doubt and disbelief shatter the effect.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Wonderbedlam","somaCost":1,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Wonderbedlam","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.lucid-madness","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332116,"modifiedTime":1784280332116,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"zQVO3qlJEbbBcaLe","name":"The Forgotten Queen","type":"gift","img":"icons/equipment/head/crown-thorns-gold-purple.webp","effects":[],"folder":"w2iwfAAiKgY8WEii","flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","contentKey":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.the-forgotten-queen","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>**SPECIAL GIFT FOR REGINA THE THIEF OF HEARTS ONLY.** Confusing flashbacks and painful emotions grip your mind as you explore Wonder. You've been here before as a patient, but the memories are fragmented and unclear. Something terrible happened to you in this place, something Alice Liddell tried to erase. Are you sure you want to remember? Once per Scene, you can attempt to remember something from your forgotten time in Wonder. Choose a specific place (Rabbit Hole, Labyrinth of Doors, Caterpillars' Greenhouse, Basement, Hall of the Mind) or a specific subject (Alice, Hatta, Cheshire, a Patient, the White Rabbits, Wonder itself). The Storyteller will give you one piece of useful information about that place or subject: a hidden Descriptor, a secret Gift they possess, their true Agenda, a weakness, or a crucial detail about how they function. This insider knowledge can be invaluable for navigating Wonder and confronting Alice. However, remembering is intensely painful—these are memories Alice tried to destroy for a reason. For the rest of the Scene after remembering, whenever you use one of your own Gifts, roll 1 die. On a result of 5 or 6, you lose 1 Soma as the mental strain overwhelms you, and you are no longer so sure that you are the Queen. Your identity begins to fragment and blur, just as Alice intended.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Wonderbedlam","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Wonderbedlam","source":"Wonderbedlam","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.wonderbedlam.the-forgotten-queen","scenario":"Wonderbedlam","scenarioSlug":"wonderbedlam","sourceDirectory":"wonderbedlam","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332116,"modifiedTime":1784280332116,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
